			<div class="col-md-11 col-sm-11 col-xs-12 no-padding">
				<h1>Weak passwords and ancient software left U.S. Government data vulnerable, DHS report finds</h1>
<div class="excerpt">Weak passwords and rarely updated software are a recurring theme behind the 48,000 cyber incidents reported to the Department of Homeland Security -  including  the theft of data on the nation’s weakest dams by a “malicious intruder”, a DHS report has found. </div>
<div class="post-meta">
    <div class="wls-authors">
            </div>
    <span class="meta">
		<span class="strong">
			<time datetime="2014-02-05 04:01:15">5 Feb 2014 - 04:01AM</time>
		</span>
			</span>
</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>	

            <div class="content">
                <div class="social-wrapper" id="social-sharer">
